feature_bullets: Commercial grade On/Off Paddle light switch is made of high-quality materials; impact resistant polycarbonate thermoplastic and solid steel. Device dimensions (excluding mounting yoke): 2. 76” H x 1. 40” W x 1. 07” D
Shallow body design fits standard junction boxes. Back insert and side terminal wiring (copper only). Break-off plaster ears. Grounding screw
Suitable for offices, schools, stores, shops, restaurants, public facilities, hotels, and residential areas that allow 20A switches.
Use with ENERLITES wall plates for the best fit and color match, part numbers SI8831-W, 8831-W standard size, 8831M-W mid-size, or 8831O-W oversize

customer_reviews.review_title: 5.0 out of 5 stars20 amp for garbage disposal switch is a good thing
customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2024
customer_reviews.review_snippet: Wanted to change from an old-style switch to a new paddle switch.  I went to local hardware store for a 20-amp decorator switch and was told they didn't believe such a switch was available in the paddle style.  Checked Amazon web site and sure enough there was exactly what I needed so I am very happy with my new switch.

customer_reviews.review_title: 5.0 out of 5 starsCRITICAL DIMENSION: Check electrical box for fit. Must be 2.75" minimum vertical.
customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2020
customer_reviews.review_snippet: Apparently 2,75" is the standard. My electrical box measured less than that so I couldn't install them. I suspect my plastic box got squeezed at the original installation. I'm doing a remove and replace of the switches, so a different box is not a convenient option. Not able to return these switches so I'm taking the loss. Have found and purchased others that will fit. Switches work and appear to be well made so I have no complaints.

customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2023
customer_reviews.review_snippet: I purchased heavy duty switches from Home Depot.  These are identical.  My electricians could not tell the difference of these switches.  These are also heavy duty.  Fast delivery.

customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2025
customer_reviews.review_snippet: These are the worst! I am building a house. I purchased 30 of these, paid an electrician to install them, then they wouldn't toggle into place. Once we had all the power on, some switches would stay on and not toggle off, some wouldn't even toggle on. I had to pay and electrician to remove and reinstall ones purchased from Home Depot. They were a disappointment. However, I did catch them on the last day of the return time frame and was able to get the money back from purchasing. Now I am just out the money of having to pay and electrician twice.

customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on May 4, 2025
customer_reviews.review_snippet: Bought for some flips, couple switches came broken but overall great for price.

customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on February 29, 2020
customer_reviews.review_snippet: I have bought hundreds of these for houses always a different brand than this. This is the first time i haven had a blinker in the group.All of them worked as advertised i will use these these from now on.

customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2022
customer_reviews.review_snippet: Same as the store offers. Much Much cheaper.

customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 2, 2021
customer_reviews.review_snippet: Time will tell about their quality???So far, So good!They function as their supposed to
